Maggot Dictionary
=================
    It's a pure python (for now console based) dictionary

Supported Formats:
    * DICT   (.dict|.idx)
    * Lingvo (.dsl)

Futures:
    * Bash completion
    * Colored output
    * Compatbile with python 3
    * Fast | Lightweight | Extensible

Dependencies
============
    Only python

Install
=======
    From archive:
        python setup.py install

    From git:
        git clone git://github.com/aslpavel/maggot-dict.git maggot-dict
        cd maggot-dict
        git submodule update --init --recursive
        python setup.py install

    For Arch Linux users:
        There is PKGBUILD script inside aur directory

Dictionary Installation
=======================
    Put dictionary files inside either:
        XDG_DATA_HOME/maggot-dict (usually '$HOME/.local/share/maggot-dict')
        XDG_DATA_DIRS/maggot-dict (usually '/usr/share/maggot-dict:/usr/share/local/maggot-dict')

